per is mostly an implementation mirror. Keep only if you want the integration test to prove stored turn keys use the algorithm; otherwise delete the helper assertion.\\n\\n**Must Stay**\\n\\n- `transcript.rs:573`, `:585`, `:595` malformed final line, malformed middle line, and empty-line index behavior. These are exactly the playbook’s high-value parser tests.\\n- `gitmeta/tests.rs:303` idempotent capture/readback. Core storage contract.\\n- `gitmeta/tests.rs:1070` growing transcripts append only new records and link turns.\\n- `gitmeta/tests.rs:1111` previous-turn selection by entry timestamp. Weird storage-order regression, worth keeping.\\n- `gitmeta/tests.rs:1173` fixed turn-key vector. Contract-level, not fluff.\\n- `redaction.rs:170`, `:204` redaction tests. Privacy-critical.\\n- `capture_lock.rs:55` lock exclusion. Small and directly protects hook races.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:16:11.414Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}